article.headline: Dartmouth 50, Princeton 42
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. (AP) -- Mike Lang scored a game-high 16 points as Dartmouth defeated Princeton 50-42 Friday night. The Big Green (5-13 overall, 2-3 Ivy) broke a seven-game losing streak against the Tigers (10-7 overall, 1-2 Ivy), the preseason favorite to win the Ivy League title. Dartmouth used an 18-1 run in the final 4:47 of the game, recovering from a nine-point deficit, 41-32. Lang scored nine of his points in that stretch, including a pair of free throws with 1:18 to play, giving Dartmouth the lead, 43-41, for the first time in the game. On the next possession, Princeton's Judson Wallace made one of two free throws for a 43-42 score with 1:06 to go. Dartmouth answered with the last seven points of the game, including a layup by David Gardner for a three-point cushion, 45-42, with 36 seconds remaining. Also in double figures for Dartmouth was Chuck Flynn with 10 points. He also had a game-high seven rebounds as the Big Green outrebounded Princeton, 24-16. For the Tigers, Noah Savage scored 10 points and added five boards.
